{"id":707344,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leon_Cooper","text":"Leon N Cooper (born February 28, 1930) is an American physicist. He won the Nobel Prize for Physics with John Bardeen and John Robert Schrieffer in 1972. He helped developed the BCS theory of superconductivity.\nHe is also the namesake of the Cooper pair and co-developer of the BCM theory of synaptic plasticity.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Americans","surface_form":"American","offset":45},{"uri":"Nobel_Prize_for_Physics","surface_form":"Nobel Prize for Physics","offset":76},{"uri":"John_Bardeen","surface_form":"John Bardeen","offset":105},{"uri":"John_Robert_Schrieffer","surface_form":"John Robert Schrieffer","offset":122},{"uri":"BCS_theory","surface_form":"BCS theory","offset":178},{"uri":"Superconductivity","surface_form":"superconductivity","offset":192},{"uri":"Cooper_pair","surface_form":"Cooper pair","offset":242},{"uri":"BCM_theory","surface_form":"BCM theory","offset":278},{"uri":"Synaptic_plasticity","surface_form":"synaptic plasticity","offset":292}]}